In fairness, Java doesn&#x27;t need to be as verbose as the &quot;Java-style code&quot; from the talk, especially now that Java 8 (with lambdas) is out. Here&#x27;s how I would write the code in Java:<p><pre><code>    runWithNetworkElement(&quot;171.0.2.45&quot;, networkElement -> {
        for (Route route : networkElement.routingTable()) {
            System.out.printf(&quot;%15s -> %s%n&quot;, route.name(), route.ipaddr());
        }
    });</code></pre>
